column5: Can anyone tell me if this lake is stocked with lakers and how the fishing is using down riggers?  What kind of lures work best?  Thanks
Not sure about the fishing there (notice I'm "Nofish4me"). Silver Lake P.P. is a great park. See lots of people fishing, not sure what they're catching.
Ontario parks web site says "Northern Pike, Smallmouth Bass, Lake Trout, Yellow Perch, and sunfish". Doesn't mention stocking.
Silver Lake is a stocked lake and is open all year for Lakers. Not a big enough hole out there to worry about using riggers. Jig for them...
On the lake contour map the deepest part is 72 feet for 2 km in length....
What is the public boat launch like....can I get a 16.5 foot boat in easily...
Don't know.. it was pretty snowed in last time I used it !
